<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5065546>
    dc:description "FIGURE 47. Braya psittacus n. g., n. sp. from the atrium (heart) of Scarus ghobban off Heron Island. Adult, whole mount, ventral view. Scale­bar: 250 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5065546/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5065550>
    dc:description "FIGURES 48–50. Braya psittacus n. g., n. sp. 48. A,B. Anterior region, ventral view. Arrow indicates thin septum separating the vestigial oral sucker from body proper. Spines not seen on specimens due to small size of vestigial oral sucker. 49. A,B. Male terminal genitalia, ventral view. Seminal vesicle extends from arrow “a” to arrow “b”. 50. Female terminal genitalia, ventral view. Vitelline duct and vitelline reservoir omitted from figure as they obscure the path of the oviducal seminal receptacle and uterus as they pass posteriorly. Scale­bars: 48A, 49A, 50, 200 m; 48B, 49B, 100 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5065550/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

